ZH: 这个月的债务还没还清。
EN: The debt for this month has not been paid off yet.

ZH: 我们需要找到一个解决债务问题的办法。
EN: We need to find a solution to the debt problem.

ZH: 他欠了我一笔债，但一直没有还。
EN: He owes me a debt, but has not paid it back yet.

ZH: 这家公司正面临着巨大的债务危机。
EN: This company is facing a huge debt crisis.

ZH: 政府正在努力降低国家的债务负担。
EN: The government is working hard to reduce the national debt burden.

ZH: 不要轻易借钱给别人，以免留下债务。
EN: Do not easily lend money to others, in order to avoid creating debt.

ZH: 我们需要做好每月的财务规划，以避免产生额外的债务。
EN: We need to make a monthly financial plan to avoid incurring additional debt.

ZH: 如果你无法偿还债务，应该及时与债权人沟通。
EN: If you are unable to repay your debt, you should communicate with your creditors in a timely manner.

ZH: 做生意一定要注意不要陷入债务漩涡。
EN: Be careful not to get caught in the debt spiral when doing business.

ZH: 建立健康的消费习惯，可以避免不必要的债务。
EN: Establishing healthy spending habits can help avoid unnecessary debt.

ZH: 还清债务后，我们终于可以松一口气了。
EN: After paying off the debt, we can finally breathe a sigh of relief.

ZH: 夫妻之间要互相支持，共同承担家庭的债务。
EN: Couples should support each other and share the family debt burden together.

ZH: 财务状况不佳时，不要将债务问题拖延下去。
EN: When in poor financial condition, do not postpone the debt issue.

ZH: 我们应当控制好债务规模，避免过度借贷。
EN: We should control the size of our debt and avoid excessive borrowing.

ZH: 如果感觉无法偿还债务，可以申请债务重组。
EN: If you feel unable to repay your debt, you can apply for debt restructuring.

ZH: 收入不稳定的人不宜轻易增加债务。
EN: People with unstable income should not easily increase their debt.

ZH: 他为了挽救公司，毅然决定清偿所有债务。
EN: In order to save the company, he decided to pay off all the debts.

ZH: 债务问题是需要认真面对和解决的。
EN: The debt problem needs to be faced and resolved seriously.

ZH: 理性消费，避免不必要的债务。
EN: Spend wisely and avoid unnecessary debt.

ZH: 有些债务是无法立即偿还的，可以提出分期付款的要求。
EN: Some debts cannot be repaid immediately, and you can request installment payments.
